      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Commentary: P0797"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P0797",
      "text": "DTC P0797: Clutch pressure control SOL.V. ON Solidification"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "130_3.0_jpn_11033655_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The clutch pressure control SOL.V. controls the hydraulic pressure in the hydraulic circuit. The spool in the clutch pressure control SOL.V. pushes a valve in response to the duty (load) output, which is converted to a current value by the PGM-FI ECU. As a result, the valve pushed by the spool releases oil pressure proportional to the current value. The PGM-FI ECU outputs a clutch pressure control SOL.V. control signal to provide the appropriate forward/reverse clutch hydraulic pressure supply. If the lock-up clutch is stuck ON, or if the time from the start of in-gear (driving force transmission state) operation to the completion of in-gear is short, the PGM-FI ECU judges that the clutch pressure control SOL.V. is stuck ON and stores DTC."
    },
