    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reproducibility Testing Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "130_3.0_jpn_11033656_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Start the engine."
        },
        {
          "text": "Step on the brake pedal and move the select lever from the N to D position."
        },
        {
          "text": "Drive until the vehicle speed [vehicle speed] reaches 60 km/h."
        },
        {
          "text": "Decelerate/stop."
        },
        {
          "text": "Set the select lever to the N position."
        },
        {
          "text": "Repeat test run steps 2 through 5 five times."
        },
        {
          "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode."
        },
        {
          "text": "Repeat test run steps 1 through 7 five times."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When conducting test drives, the driver must comply with all laws and regulations, observe good manners, and drive in accordance with the surrounding conditions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to have a fault, a temporary DTC is stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory. If the same failure is detected at the next D/C (two consecutive detections), the D indicator light will flash without the PGM-FI warning light illuminating, and the DTC and freeze data will be stored."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use of the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or removal of the 12V battery terminal will clear the D indicator light, temporary DTC, DTC, and freeze data."
    }
  ],
